value.title: Washington Post: CIA assessment says Putin 'probably directing' efforts to interfere in 2020 election against Biden
value.excerpt: The CIA assessed in August that Russian President Vladimir Putin and his top aides "are aware of and probably directing Russia's influence operations" aimed at undermining Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden in the 2020 election, according to a new report in The Washington Post.
